=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_TDelay_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 441 Hz, featuring very_slow attack and dynamic envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: very_slow
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: very_dynamic
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 441.2715
  harmonic_decay_rate: -7.2962
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5161
  pitch_clarity: 21.7856
  inharmonicity: 0.0035
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -2.9075
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: TDelay Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/TDelay.html
// Tags: TDelay, Classes, reverb
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
(
{
    z = Impulse.ar(2);
    [z * 0.1, ToggleFF.ar(TDelay.ar(z, 0.5)) * SinOsc.ar(mul: 0.1)]
}.play)
